Prof: There are reasons,
other reasons in India,

00:07:43.702 --> 00:07:46.632
there's clearly reasons all
around and they may be different

00:07:46.632 --> 00:07:49.709
in different places but the main
hypothesis that we are working

00:07:49.709 --> 00:07:52.680
on it and come back to it,
it's very important.

00:07:52.680 --> 00:07:56.177
The main hypothesis that we're
working on is that it's one

00:07:56.177 --> 00:07:57.649
child policy in China.
 

00:07:57.649 --> 00:08:01.535
Now we see that China is not
particularly extreme say

00:08:01.535 --> 00:08:03.028
compared to India.
 

00:08:03.028 --> 00:08:05.341
It depends on what year you
look and exactly what statistic

00:08:05.341 --> 00:08:05.899
you look at.
 

00:08:05.899 --> 00:08:08.269
It's really in the same
ballpark with India.

00:08:08.269 --> 00:08:11.706
Now we have to say that well,
it's probably not one child

00:08:11.706 --> 00:08:12.259
policy.
 

00:08:12.259 --> 00:08:16.000
What's our next hypothesis?
 

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:18.339
We've heard a different one for
China.

00:08:18.339 --> 00:08:22.774
India has bride price but than
if you start with India and say

00:08:22.774 --> 00:08:25.610
that, China doesn't have bride
price;

00:08:25.610 --> 00:08:30.088
they have dowry,
they may have in fact the

00:08:30.088 --> 00:08:31.290
opposite.
 

00:08:31.290 --> 00:08:33.567
What about--
Student:  Is it sex

00:08:33.567 --> 00:08:34.450
selective abortion?
 

00:08:34.450 --> 00:08:36.428
Prof: That's something,
but why are the women doing it?

00:08:36.428 --> 00:08:39.567
Poverty, that's the usual thing
when you speak of India and

00:08:39.567 --> 00:08:40.000
China.
 

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:45.303
In these years they were still
very--they're still quite poor

00:08:45.303 --> 00:08:47.158
but it was poverty.
 

00:08:47.158 --> 00:08:54.048
How does that strike you as a
hypothesis for this?

00:08:54.048 --> 00:08:57.750
Or part of it,
these things are multi-causal.

00:08:57.750 --> 00:09:00.274
Student:  China's
economy has been taking off but

00:09:00.274 --> 00:09:02.019
it's the--ratios are still going
up.

00:09:02.019 --> 00:09:04.520
Prof: Well the only--
I'm going to show you that data

00:09:04.520 --> 00:09:06.428
but I only showed you the data
up to 1990,

00:09:06.428 --> 00:09:12.750
1992 so I haven't--I'm going to
show you that.

00:09:12.750 --> 00:09:16.466
Again we can go to an
international comparison if we

00:09:16.466 --> 00:09:19.745
want to see if poverty is at the
root of this,

00:09:19.745 --> 00:09:22.370
and what are we looking at
here?

00:09:22.370 --> 00:09:24.200
Korea, South Korea.
 

00:09:24.200 --> 00:09:29.456
Korea is not a poor country and
yet they're just as bad,

00:09:29.456 --> 00:09:35.190
in fact a little bit more
extreme than China at this time.

00:09:35.190 --> 00:09:39.163
We really have quite a
conundrum that we can give

00:09:39.163 --> 00:09:44.461
particular explanations for each
place but they're maybe going to

00:09:44.461 --> 00:09:45.870
be different.
 

00:09:45.870 --> 00:09:48.981
Student:  Is it maybe
just population growth in

00:09:48.981 --> 00:09:49.570
general?
 

00:09:49.570 --> 00:09:52.413
Prof: It could be
population growth in general,

00:09:52.413 --> 00:09:55.308
that's certainly true of all of
the three countries.

00:09:55.308 --> 00:09:57.950
That there's something about
the density of population;

00:09:57.950 --> 00:10:02.461
hard to prove since India and
China have been very crowded for

00:10:02.461 --> 00:10:06.307
a very long time and Korea is
also crowded but not as

00:10:06.307 --> 00:10:08.750
extremely as China and India.
 

00:10:16.320 --> 00:10:21.558
Not--the greatest sex ratio is
in South Korea,

00:10:21.558 --> 00:10:25.907
which is, as you heard,
is not poor and by 2010 there

00:10:25.907 --> 00:10:29.668
will be a 20% deficit in the
marriage age,

00:10:29.668 --> 00:10:34.666
there will be a 20% deficit of
females in Korea which is quite

00:10:34.666 --> 00:10:37.370
high and that's done away with.
 

00:10:37.370 --> 00:10:41.495
The poverty thing,
the economic thing does not

00:10:41.495 --> 00:10:44.996
work between countries,
and even if you look,

00:10:44.996 --> 00:10:46.860
I'll show you a little bit
later,

00:10:46.860 --> 00:10:51.153
there's big regional variations
within each country but it

00:10:51.153 --> 00:10:53.788
doesn't go with economics at
all.

00:10:53.788 --> 00:10:58.265
In China, in Guangdong,
where everything you're wearing

00:10:58.265 --> 00:11:03.250
and everything you play with,
including probably this is made

00:11:03.250 --> 00:11:06.408
somewhere in Guangdong Province
probably.

00:11:06.408 --> 00:11:11.140
It's one of the richer places
in China and the sex ratio there

00:11:11.140 --> 00:11:14.568
is 130 to 100,
something I've showed you 12 to

00:11:14.568 --> 00:11:16.748
14,
in that province it goes up to

00:11:16.748 --> 00:11:20.254
130 and parts of that province--
so of course even within a

00:11:20.254 --> 00:11:22.308
province there's different
places,

00:11:22.308 --> 00:11:26.778
they can go up to 144 to 100,
so something like a third of

00:11:26.778 --> 00:11:29.210
the girls are done away with.
 

00:11:29.210 --> 00:11:33.160
Student:  Provinces with
such a skewed sex ratio,

00:11:33.160 --> 00:11:37.184
do they end up paying dowry or
these bride prices because

00:11:37.184 --> 00:11:38.908
females are so rare?
 

00:11:38.908 --> 00:11:42.028
Prof: No bride price
doesn't happen in either China

00:11:42.028 --> 00:11:43.264
or India;
bride price,

00:11:43.264 --> 00:11:45.541
you remember,
is when the man's family gives

00:11:45.541 --> 00:11:48.029
something to the girl or the
girl's family,

00:11:48.029 --> 00:11:54.562
dowry is the opposite and dowry
is common in India and really it

00:11:54.562 --> 00:11:57.466
was--
communists got rid of it,

00:11:57.466 --> 00:12:02.080
any vestige of that in China so
that's not the case.

00:12:02.080 --> 00:12:07.004
In India the same thing,
the states in New Delhi and

00:12:07.004 --> 00:12:11.061
Haryana, which are the richer
places there,

00:12:11.061 --> 00:12:15.889
have more extreme sex ratios
then poor places.

00:12:15.889 --> 00:12:24.748
There's--in Delhi there's 861
females per 1,000 males at birth

00:12:24.748 --> 00:12:32.445
and so as time goes on,
as you see, the sex ratios are

00:12:32.445 --> 00:12:35.058
getting worse.
 

00:12:35.058 --> 00:12:40.390
The answer to our problem of
what is causing--what caused

00:12:40.390 --> 00:12:45.913
things to change at this point
in time is what someone here

