India--went to England and
observed things and came back

00:30:47.394 --> 00:30:51.455
and wrote a travel book for the
Chinese and this is a quote from

00:30:51.455 --> 00:30:55.453
that: "England is so short
of inhabitants that the English

00:30:55.453 --> 00:30:57.838
rear every child that is born.
 

00:30:57.838 --> 00:31:01.255
Even prostitutes who bear
children do not destroy

00:31:01.255 --> 00:31:02.180
them."
 

00:31:02.180 --> 00:31:06.069
England was the dominant power
of the world and they were

00:31:06.069 --> 00:31:08.710
invading China with the Opium
Wars,

00:31:08.710 --> 00:31:10.964
so of course everybody
including the Emperor was

00:31:10.964 --> 00:31:12.788
interested in what is England
like,

00:31:12.788 --> 00:31:16.230
how come they're so powerful,
what's different there,

00:31:16.230 --> 00:31:20.028
and so the Emperor read this
and the Emperor's response was,

00:31:20.028 --> 00:31:23.980
he didn't believe that the
English were so stupid.

00:31:23.980 --> 00:31:28.519
Again, the cultural thing that
to raise up all the children,

00:31:28.519 --> 00:31:33.288
and especially to raise up all
the girls, is just not going.

00:31:33.288 --> 00:31:37.549
In your reading packet,
it discusses villages in India

00:31:37.549 --> 00:31:41.410
dating back to 1830 that have no
girls at all.

00:31:41.410 --> 00:31:45.848
They just do away with all the
girls, all of them are killed.

00:31:45.848 --> 00:31:50.880
1921, Somerset Maugham,
does that name ring any bells?

00:31:50.880 --> 00:31:53.803
He was a famous author,
wrote a lot of novels,

00:31:53.803 --> 00:31:56.661
a lot of movies with very
famous movie stars,

00:31:56.661 --> 00:31:58.348
a very popular author.
 

00:31:58.348 --> 00:32:02.279
In 1921 he was touring China
and he came upon a little tower

00:32:02.279 --> 00:32:06.410
on a Chinese hillside with a
single small hole in the wall,

00:32:06.410 --> 00:32:09.898
so they're walking along and
there's a small tower with a

00:32:09.898 --> 00:32:11.519
little hole in the wall.
 

00:32:11.519 --> 00:32:16.710
Out of that hole came a
nauseating odor and he asked--

00:32:16.710 --> 00:32:19.880
he was with a Chinese guide and
he asked him what is that,

00:32:19.880 --> 00:32:23.348
and he thought maybe feces were
dumped there or something.

00:32:23.348 --> 00:32:27.571
No, it turns out it was a baby
tower and it was just a pit dug

00:32:27.571 --> 00:32:31.448
into the ground and surrounded
with this tower and people

00:32:31.448 --> 00:32:36.388
brought excess girls especially,
but some occasionally boys and

00:32:36.388 --> 00:32:38.608
just dumped them into this.
 

00:32:38.608 --> 00:32:41.780
A little boy came up and
explained this to him and said

00:32:41.780 --> 00:32:45.365
that--the little boy said that
four babies were thrown in that

00:32:45.365 --> 00:32:46.068
morning.
 

00:32:46.068 --> 00:32:49.335
This doesn't--this particular
passage didn't discuss the sex

00:32:49.335 --> 00:32:52.655
of the babies because he didn't
know that, they're already in

00:32:52.655 --> 00:32:53.210
there.
 

00:32:53.210 --> 00:32:56.733
One of the quotes is,
"The female child is

00:32:56.733 --> 00:32:59.108
regarded as a liability here.
 

00:32:59.108 --> 00:33:02.618
In rural areas women are not
even considered people."

00:33:02.618 --> 00:33:07.005
You'll do some reading where,
rather biased reading but

00:33:07.005 --> 00:33:10.627
accurate on this,
that girls often don't get

00:33:10.627 --> 00:33:14.384
names traditionally,
their named 'daughter number

00:33:14.384 --> 00:33:18.807
one,' 'daughter number two,'
'daughter number three,' and all

00:33:18.807 --> 00:33:20.210
kinds of things.
 

00:33:20.210 --> 00:33:23.895
As I've mentioned the
elimination of females is not

00:33:23.895 --> 00:33:27.730
limited to the young and in one
of your readings--

00:33:27.730 --> 00:33:32.333
I guess I described it to you,
a tribe in New Guinea where if

00:33:32.333 --> 00:33:36.170
a male died his widow was
immediately strangled.

00:33:36.170 --> 00:33:37.609
Do you remember that?
 

00:33:37.609 --> 00:33:40.910
That changes the sex ratio.
 

00:33:40.910 --> 00:33:44.532
In India, you've all heard
about this, they're used to be a

00:33:44.532 --> 00:33:46.970
variant to this practice called
sati.

00:33:46.970 --> 00:33:50.782
You heard of sati or sutee,
sometime where the wife throws

00:33:50.782 --> 00:33:54.663
herself on the funeral pyre of
the man or in some other way

00:33:54.663 --> 00:33:56.470
does away with herself.
 

00:33:56.470 --> 00:33:59.288
This is from 1813,
quite some time back,

00:33:59.288 --> 00:34:03.950
and there was a British captain
named Kemp who was eyewitness to

00:34:03.950 --> 00:34:08.018
one of these things and he wrote
a description of it.

00:34:08.018 --> 00:34:10.639
" A male had been sick a
short time.

00:34:10.639 --> 00:34:14.592
An astrologer said that he was
on the point of death and so he

00:34:14.592 --> 00:34:18.739
was taken down to the side of
the holy Ganges River to expire.

00:34:18.739 --> 00:34:22.083
He was immersed to his waist in
the river for some time,

00:34:22.083 --> 00:34:23.300
but he didn't die.
 

00:34:23.300 --> 00:34:27.619
They brought him back to the
bank of the river and let him

00:34:27.619 --> 00:34:29.989
broil in the sun;
he didn't die.

00:34:29.989 --> 00:34:32.710
Then they put him back in the
river again, and he didn't die.

00:34:32.710 --> 00:34:34.518
He was returned to the
bank."

00:34:34.518 --> 00:34:38.534
This kept going for 36 hours
alternating sort of freezing and

00:34:38.534 --> 00:34:41.210
baking and finally this sick guy
died.

00:34:41.210 --> 00:34:42.809
Whether he would,
or would not,

00:34:42.809 --> 00:34:44.409
have died anyway,
who knows.

00:34:44.409 --> 00:34:48.030
It was the astrologer's word
that he was going to die.

00:34:48.030 --> 00:34:52.016
His wife, he was married,
was a healthy young girl of

00:34:52.016 --> 00:34:52.860
about 16.
 

00:34:52.860 --> 00:34:57.809
Learning of her husband's death
she decided to be buried alive

00:34:57.809 --> 00:34:59.268
with his corpse.
 

00:34:59.268 --> 00:35:01.875
The British officer,
this Kemp, tried in vain to

00:35:01.875 --> 00:35:05.833
persuade the girl not to do it,
then tried to persuade the

00:35:05.833 --> 00:35:10.378
mother, and he said that a
resolution of this type to just

00:35:10.378 --> 00:35:13.489
kill yourself was a kind of
madness.

00:35:13.489 --> 00:35:16.637
He had no success and he
encountered not the slightest

00:35:16.637 --> 00:35:19.961
sign of either hesitation or a
great regret on either the

00:35:19.961 --> 00:35:22.159
girl's part or the mother's
part.

00:35:22.159 --> 00:35:27.202
The actual scene takes place;
the young widow accompanied by

00:35:27.202 --> 00:35:30.820
her friends proceeded to the
beach where his body lay.

00:35:30.820 --> 00:35:34.101
He was placed in a grave about
six feet deep,

00:35:34.101 --> 00:35:37.829
the wife circled the grave
seven times calling out,

00:35:37.829 --> 00:35:40.440
"Hail God,
Hail God."

00:35:40.440 --> 00:35:43.420
the surrounding crowd echoed
her chant, 'Hail God,

00:35:43.420 --> 00:35:44.150
Hail God.'
 

00:35:44.150 --> 00:35:47.329
She climbed into the grave,
the captain,

00:35:47.329 --> 00:35:50.657
this British guy moved up to
within a foot of the grave to

00:35:50.657 --> 00:35:54.101
see if at the last minute she
showed any signs of reluctance

00:35:54.101 --> 00:35:57.369
or whether her relatives showed
any sign of horror,

00:35:57.369 --> 00:36:00.358
and if she showed reluctance he
might have jumped in and pulled

00:36:00.358 --> 00:36:00.840
her out.
 

00:36:00.840 --> 00:36:03.449
She placed herself in a sitting
posture,

00:36:03.449 --> 00:36:06.137
as her husband had been placed,
didn't lay him flat but a

00:36:06.137 --> 00:36:08.300
sitting posture,
both faced north,

00:36:08.300 --> 00:36:10.949
so she was sitting behind his
back.

00:36:10.949 --> 00:36:14.902
She embraced the corpse with
her left hand and reclined her

00:36:14.902 --> 00:36:16.469
head on his shoulder.
 

00:36:16.469 --> 00:36:20.260
The British officer still saw
no sign of regret on her part.

00:36:20.260 --> 00:36:23.871
The other plan--the other hand
she placed over her head with

00:36:23.871 --> 00:36:27.730
her forefinger erect which she
moved in a circular direction.

00:36:27.730 --> 00:36:33.773
The watchers then started
throwing earth on them to start

00:36:33.773 --> 00:36:39.293
burying them and then other men,
as the earth was put in,

00:36:39.293 --> 00:36:43.505
they stamped on the earth to
pack it down but she continued

00:36:43.505 --> 00:36:48.007
circling her hand until her head
was completely buried and then

00:36:48.007 --> 00:36:52.730
she kept going for some time
after that and finally stopped.

00:36:52.730 --> 00:36:55.990
The earth was piled on and
stamped down and was two or

00:36:55.990 --> 00:36:58.760
three feet above the heads of
the entombed.

00:36:58.760 --> 00:37:01.710
No tear was shed by any of the
relations.

00:37:01.710 --> 00:37:05.583
Eventually the crowd disbursed
and the ritual lamentations and

00:37:05.583 --> 00:37:08.059
howling commenced but without
sorrow.

00:37:08.059 --> 00:37:14.112
This is a long time ago and
it's certainly extremely rare

00:37:14.112 --> 00:37:17.139
now, if it happens at all.
 

00:37:17.139 --> 00:37:20.704
There was one report of one
woman in a village about ten

00:37:20.704 --> 00:37:23.967
years ago who did it,
and this is illegal in India,

00:37:23.967 --> 00:37:26.559
so very hard to get any decent
statistics,

00:37:26.559 --> 00:37:30.592
but very rarely it happens and
this woman who killed herself on

00:37:30.592 --> 00:37:33.974
her husband's pyre was
considered a paragon of virtue

00:37:33.974 --> 00:37:37.681
and sort of like a saint because
she was following the old

00:37:37.681 --> 00:37:40.998
religious customs and the
village was happy about it

00:37:40.998 --> 00:37:44.706
because they got a lot of
tourists to come and revere this

00:37:44.706 --> 00:37:49.130
saint like lady and made a lot
of money off the tourists,

00:37:49.130 --> 00:37:54.460
but it's very rare.
 

00:37:54.460 --> 00:37:58.568
Of course this whole sex
preference business is not in

00:37:58.568 --> 00:38:00.739
any sense limited to Asia.
 

00:38:00.739 --> 00:38:04.061
Hispanic women in Los Angeles
were surveyed,

00:38:04.061 --> 00:38:07.692
they want 2.8 sons on average
and 0.1 daughters,

00:38:07.692 --> 00:38:10.010
a factor of 28 difference.
 

00:38:10.010 --> 00:38:15.775
In Kuwait before the Gulf War,
this is the 1991 war I think,

00:38:15.775 --> 00:38:21.054
Barbara Walters who you all
know, did a story on gender

00:38:21.054 --> 00:38:23.010
roles in Kuwait.
 

00:38:23.010 --> 00:38:25.079
Yes, during the Gulf War she
was there,

00:38:25.079 --> 00:38:28.235
and she noted that women
customarily walked about ten

00:38:28.235 --> 00:38:32.239
feet behind their husbands and
this happens in a lot of places,

00:38:32.239 --> 00:38:35.139
and a strong sign of female
deference and dependence.

00:38:35.139 --> 00:38:38.987
The husband walks without the
wife and the wife follows ten

00:38:38.987 --> 00:38:41.840
feet behind, you've heard of
that custom.

00:38:41.840 --> 00:38:47.590
The war takes place,
the Iraqi's get beaten,

00:38:47.590 --> 00:38:51.820
she comes back to Kuwait to do
another story after the war,

00:38:51.820 --> 00:38:56.835
and she was so pleased because
now the men walked behind the

00:38:56.835 --> 00:38:58.925
wives,
that the women were walking in

00:38:58.925 --> 00:39:00.503
front,
and so Barbara Walters said

00:39:00.503 --> 00:39:03.797
this is wonderful progress,
this is the American--they're

00:39:03.797 --> 00:39:07.891
catching on over there and so
she approached one of the women

00:39:07.891 --> 00:39:10.097
and said--
and the camera was rolling to

00:39:10.097 --> 00:39:11.806
catch this,
she's a TV personality,

00:39:11.806 --> 00:39:14.429
"this is marvelous,"
says Barbara Walters,

00:39:14.429 --> 00:39:18.402
"can you tell the free
world just what enabled women to

00:39:18.402 --> 00:39:21.030
achieve this reversal of
roles?"

00:39:21.030 --> 00:39:27.909
The Kuwaiti woman said,
"Land mines."

00:39:27.909 --> 00:39:33.380
And so it wasn't a reversal at
all.

00:39:33.380 --> 00:39:43.170
I think you get the idea of all
of this.

00:39:43.170 --> 00:39:47.096
We--there's deeper reasons,
I mean again one way is to put

00:39:47.096 --> 00:39:51.367
it down to Asian tradition and
that's not really any kind of an

00:39:51.367 --> 00:39:52.469
explanation.
 

00:39:52.469 --> 00:39:55.503
We like to think that people
are rational around the world

00:39:55.503 --> 00:39:58.429
and that there's some more
fundamental reason for it.

00:39:58.429 --> 00:40:01.679
A lot of the reasons that you
all said, what are some of the

00:40:01.679 --> 00:40:04.929
extra reasons that I sort of
pushed aside for the moment?

00:40:04.929 --> 00:40:09.820
One was dowry issues and some
of you said some other things,

00:40:09.820 --> 00:40:14.809
but there's a whole lot of
things, and the basic story is

00:40:14.809 --> 00:40:17.610
that in--
certainly in India and also in

00:40:17.610 --> 00:40:21.130
traditional China the girl is
brought up by the parents,

00:40:21.130 --> 00:40:25.697
gets married at quite a young
age, and by young teenage they

00:40:25.697 --> 00:40:29.260
get married and get shipped off
to the son--

00:40:29.260 --> 00:40:32.885
the husband's family where she
works is then counted in that

00:40:32.885 --> 00:40:36.565
family and is worked--
usually works very hard and

00:40:36.565 --> 00:40:39.750
basically is a servant in that
family.

00:40:39.750 --> 00:40:44.983
The family that raises her has
the problem of investing in that

00:40:44.983 --> 00:40:48.248
girl,
putting a lot of money to raise

00:40:48.248 --> 00:40:50.469
that girl,
then, just as she's able to

00:40:50.469 --> 00:40:52.909
start working seriously and
maybe return some labor,

00:40:52.909 --> 00:40:56.789
some serious labor or some
money to the parents,

00:40:56.789 --> 00:41:01.429
she's gone and she works for
some other family.

00:41:01.429 --> 00:41:05.168
This is economically a very bad
thing and the people call

00:41:05.168 --> 00:41:08.639
raising girls like watering
someone else's garden.

00:41:08.639 --> 00:41:12.420
Then on top of that when the
dowry system is strong,

00:41:12.420 --> 00:41:15.320
which it is in India,
and going crazy,

00:41:15.320 --> 00:41:18.907
then at marriage they have to
provide a lot of money and this

00:41:18.907 --> 00:41:21.300
can go up to be like a year's
income,

00:41:21.300 --> 00:41:25.306
easily, to get the girl
married, and it's a great honor

00:41:25.306 --> 00:41:25.900
thing.
 

00:41:25.900 --> 00:41:28.818
If you have a daughter you have
to get her married,

00:41:28.818 --> 00:41:32.320
so you have to pay dowry or
your family's honor goes away.

00:41:32.320 --> 00:41:37.581
This idea, that the girl is
just passed away just at the

00:41:37.581 --> 00:41:42.862
time she can be of value to you,
is kind of the rational actor

00:41:42.862 --> 00:41:46.460
theory of why there's all this
female discrimination.

00:41:46.460 --> 00:41:51.139
Anything strike you unexplained
about that?

00:41:51.139 --> 00:41:53.920
Why is that--
Student:  It's the girl.

00:41:53.920 --> 00:41:56.789
Prof: It's the girl that
goes away all the time.

00:41:56.789 --> 00:41:58.590
Why can't the man go away?
 

00:41:58.590 --> 00:42:00.309
This is, by the way,
characteristic of human

00:42:00.309 --> 00:42:00.789
societies.
 

00:42:00.789 --> 00:42:05.045
I may have mentioned this to
you, the genetics shows that

00:42:05.045 --> 00:42:09.153
males in a village are related,
they've stayed there for

00:42:09.153 --> 00:42:13.992
hundreds or thousands of years,
and females move out,

00:42:13.992 --> 00:42:15.559
so exogamy.
 

00:42:15.559 --> 00:42:17.590
Where have you seen exogamy
before?

00:42:17.590 --> 00:42:21.840
Among the chimpanzees where the
females go out;

00:42:21.840 --> 00:42:26.197
and so as far as we can tell
this is a vestige from our very

00:42:26.197 --> 00:42:30.849
original biological roots where
our reproductive system requires

00:42:30.849 --> 00:42:35.353
not that the males fight each
other and the males disburse but

00:42:35.353 --> 00:42:39.710
that the males stay together in
a military situation and the

00:42:39.710 --> 00:42:41.409
females go out.
 

00:42:41.409 --> 00:42:45.344
It's this very basic form
of--you can call it chimpanzee

00:42:45.344 --> 00:42:48.280
social organization that leads
to that.

00:42:48.280 --> 00:42:51.074
The females go out and
therefore the females are of no

00:42:51.074 --> 00:42:54.237
value to the family that brings
them up and therefore they're

00:42:54.237 --> 00:42:55.610
discriminated against.
 

00:42:55.610 --> 00:42:58.864
The men stay together and they
have to have a

00:42:58.864 --> 00:43:02.639
protective--protect the village
against violence.

00:43:02.639 --> 00:43:05.786
In some places there's
a--either a tribe or a caste as

00:43:05.786 --> 00:43:08.695
you'll call it in India,
the Nayar, which are very

00:43:08.695 --> 00:43:10.239
military kind of cast.
 

00:43:10.239 --> 00:43:12.889
What happens is they get
married very young,

00:43:12.889 --> 00:43:15.331
but then the man may,
or may not, spend one night

00:43:15.331 --> 00:43:18.079
with the wife and then he goes
off to the military,

00:43:18.079 --> 00:43:20.228
and meanwhile,
the wife has all kinds of

00:43:20.228 --> 00:43:22.929
sexual relationships and its
quite formalized,

00:43:22.929 --> 00:43:25.230
quite legal,
the women live in one big

00:43:25.230 --> 00:43:26.543
house,
they don't really

00:43:26.543 --> 00:43:28.760
recognize--it's like the Na that
you read about,

00:43:28.760 --> 00:43:32.860
it's a female lineage society,
and then upper class men are

00:43:32.860 --> 00:43:36.961
invited in to sleep with these
women and produce babies for

00:43:36.961 --> 00:43:39.275
them,
and then the men have 15 or 20

00:43:39.275 --> 00:43:40.719
years of military service.
 

00:43:40.719 --> 00:43:44.474
Then they come home,
and only really at that time,

00:43:44.474 --> 00:43:46.849
do they pick up the marriage.
 

00:43:46.849 --> 00:43:50.795
Again it's a very clear--in
this particular cultural

00:43:50.795 --> 00:43:53.505
manifestation,
it's a very clear thing that

00:43:53.505 --> 00:43:56.449
women are the reproducers,
men are the military ones,

00:43:56.449 --> 00:44:00.206
and, as in chimpanzees,
sort of a communal sexuality

00:44:00.206 --> 00:44:05.389
that who's the biological father
is not particularly important.

00:44:13.320 --> 00:44:18.739
Now, I want to switch gears
here in the time we have left,

00:44:18.739 --> 00:44:20.619
and this whole lecture is about
South Asia,

00:44:20.619 --> 00:44:24.121
and South Asia and East Asia
are the centers of female

00:44:24.121 --> 00:44:27.228
disadvantage,
but that doesn't go on in all

00:44:27.228 --> 00:44:28.289
of South Asia.
 

00:44:28.289 --> 00:44:30.210
As I've mentioned,
in Muslim countries that

00:44:30.210 --> 00:44:31.489
basically does not happen.
 

