servants of the countries when

00:59:34.380 --> 00:59:37.130
they got independence it was the
same people,

00:59:37.130 --> 00:59:38.539
so this was in their mind.
 

00:59:38.539 --> 00:59:42.159
In fact the South Asia,
originally India and Pakistan,

00:59:42.159 --> 00:59:45.985
were some of the very first
countries to institute family

00:59:45.985 --> 00:59:47.489
planning programs.
 

00:59:47.489 --> 00:59:52.639
The one in Pakistan was not
particularly successful,

00:59:52.639 --> 00:59:55.922
the one in India is now much
better but did not start out

00:59:55.922 --> 00:59:58.163
successfully,
but after the war of

00:59:58.163 --> 01:00:01.032
independence,
when Bangladesh split from West

01:00:01.032 --> 01:00:05.139
Pakistan the government really
was aware of these problems,

01:00:05.139 --> 01:00:09.434
had a Malthusian attitude and
they really decided that they

01:00:09.434 --> 01:00:13.360
must start to get some control
of their population.

01:00:13.360 --> 01:00:17.168
The government supported and
instituted a family planning

01:00:17.168 --> 01:00:21.248
program for the whole country
and international organizations

01:00:21.248 --> 01:00:23.634
said,
'OK, you want to do this,

01:00:23.634 --> 01:00:26.905
we will help you,' and
especially there's a group

01:00:26.905 --> 01:00:30.655
called The International
Diarrheal Research Organization

01:00:30.655 --> 01:00:34.677
which was one of the ones that
had discovered and pushed the

01:00:34.677 --> 01:00:36.860
oral rehydration packets.
 

01:00:36.860 --> 01:00:41.143
Many, many--huge numbers of
infant deaths in poor countries

01:00:41.143 --> 01:00:42.762
due--
they get diarrhea and

01:00:42.762 --> 01:00:45.860
diarrhea--the bug doesn't kill
you but you lose enough water

01:00:45.860 --> 01:00:49.065
through the diarrhea that you
die basically of dehydration and

01:00:49.065 --> 01:00:52.268
all you need to do is to have a
little packet of water,

01:00:52.268 --> 01:00:56.259
salt and sugar and as long as
the water is not terribly

01:00:56.259 --> 01:01:00.543
polluted the child will stay
alive and will eventually kick

01:01:00.543 --> 01:01:03.130
out the virus or the bacterium.
 

01:01:03.130 --> 01:01:05.974
This International Diarrheal
Research Group,

01:01:05.974 --> 01:01:08.489
are very well respected,
and they said,

01:01:08.489 --> 01:01:12.659
'okay we will also help you
with family planning programs.'

01:01:12.659 --> 01:01:19.110
What resulted was a countrywide
program.

01:01:19.110 --> 01:01:22.449
Now at this same time,
we're talking the early 1970s,

01:01:22.449 --> 01:01:27.420
most of the developed world had
the idea that they--

01:01:27.420 --> 01:01:30.068
what did they say,
they saw rich countries have

01:01:30.068 --> 01:01:32.210
few children,
poor countries have a lot of

01:01:32.210 --> 01:01:33.469
children,
what's the cause?

01:01:33.469 --> 01:01:35.219
Well money is the cause.
 

01:01:35.219 --> 01:01:37.371
When you get rich you want to
have fewer children,

01:01:37.371 --> 01:01:39.701
we're going to have a lecture
on that very interesting

01:01:39.701 --> 01:01:40.360
phenomenon.
 

01:01:40.360 --> 01:01:43.824
A lot of developing countries
and East European countries

01:01:43.824 --> 01:01:47.101
rejected the whole idea of
family planning as a way of

01:01:47.101 --> 01:01:50.641
improving the economy and said,
no development is the best

01:01:50.641 --> 01:01:51.400
contraceptive.
 

01:01:51.400 --> 01:01:53.583
That was the rule,
development is the best

01:01:53.583 --> 01:01:55.472
contraceptive,
that there's no way in,

01:01:55.472 --> 01:01:57.867
a poor place like Bangladesh,
that you're going to get

01:01:57.867 --> 01:02:00.226
fertility down because of all
these reasons that we've

01:02:00.226 --> 01:02:02.144
mentioned,
but if you develop the country

01:02:02.144 --> 01:02:04.389
economically than it will
naturally come down and the

01:02:04.389 --> 01:02:06.289
government doesn't have to mess
with it,

01:02:06.289 --> 01:02:08.989
doesn't have to set up family
planning programs.

01:02:08.989 --> 01:02:12.262
Everybody predicted,
strenuously,

01:02:12.262 --> 01:02:18.295
that Bangladesh could do what
it wanted with family planning

01:02:18.295 --> 01:02:24.228
programs until and unless they
developed economically there

01:02:24.228 --> 01:02:26.989
would be no progress.
 

01:02:26.989 --> 01:02:33.443
What they did was they--prior
to this program they had tried a

01:02:33.443 --> 01:02:35.559
variety of things.
 

01:02:35.559 --> 01:02:37.949
In Pakistan one of the programs
was,

01:02:37.949 --> 01:02:41.637
well people are culturally into
having a lot of children and so

01:02:41.637 --> 01:02:45.800
we must work with their culture,
and must work with traditional

01:02:45.800 --> 01:02:47.050
birth attendants.
 

01:02:47.050 --> 01:02:49.422
In Pakistan,
including Bangladesh at the

01:02:49.422 --> 01:02:53.010
time,
they had women called Daiys who

01:02:53.010 --> 01:02:56.909
are basically local health
providers,

01:02:56.909 --> 01:03:01.284
herbal women,
midwives for births and stuff

01:03:01.284 --> 01:03:04.753
like that,
but they had basically no

01:03:04.753 --> 01:03:07.119
modern training whatsoever.
 

01:03:07.119 --> 01:03:12.306
In the first implementation of
Pakistan's program they gave

01:03:12.306 --> 01:03:17.226
these Daiys various forms of
birth control and they were

01:03:17.226 --> 01:03:19.909
supposed to give them out.
 

01:03:19.909 --> 01:03:21.239
It didn't work.
 

01:03:21.239 --> 01:03:21.909
Why didn't it work?
 

01:03:21.909 --> 01:03:25.105
The Daiys themselves were older
women in general who did not use

01:03:25.105 --> 01:03:27.539
contraception and did not think
it was moral,

01:03:27.539 --> 01:03:30.659
did not think it worked,
and had all kinds of bad

01:03:30.659 --> 01:03:32.090
attitudes toward it.
 

01:03:32.090 --> 01:03:34.623
So, if someone tries to sell
you something,

01:03:34.623 --> 01:03:36.978
and they don't themselves
believe in it,

01:03:36.978 --> 01:03:39.030
you generally don't accept it.
 

01:03:39.030 --> 01:03:41.708
Plus, economically,
they made very little by

01:03:41.708 --> 01:03:44.762
distributing these kind of
contraceptives from the

01:03:44.762 --> 01:03:48.047
government,
but they could make quite a bit

01:03:48.047 --> 01:03:52.404
more by attending the births
that they charge a good fee for

01:03:52.404 --> 01:03:56.170
births where the government set
the little bit,

01:03:56.170 --> 01:03:58.695
they wanted to have the
contraceptives very fairly free

01:03:58.695 --> 01:04:01.161
to the people,
so they didn't pay the Daiys

01:04:01.161 --> 01:04:01.820
very much.
 

01:04:01.820 --> 01:04:04.458
The Daiys would get all the
condoms especially and sort of

01:04:04.458 --> 01:04:07.235
bury them somewhere and claim to
the government that they had

01:04:07.235 --> 01:04:09.320
distributed them and then made a
lot of--

01:04:09.320 --> 01:04:12.565
not a lot of money,
but their money from attending

01:04:12.565 --> 01:04:15.679
the births that hadn't been
averted by this,

01:04:15.679 --> 01:04:17.869
so it didn't work.
 

01:04:17.869 --> 01:04:20.195
They learn, these are again the
first countries in the world to

01:04:20.195 --> 01:04:22.407
have family planning programs
and they didn't know how to do

01:04:22.407 --> 01:04:22.670
it.
 

01:04:22.670 --> 01:04:26.309
You have to--it's not given
that this is the way you do it.

01:04:26.309 --> 01:04:31.253
Eventually they started the
program that I described to you

01:04:31.253 --> 01:04:35.940
somewhat last time where the
women can't come out of the

01:04:35.940 --> 01:04:41.139
house so you hire a high status
woman from that village,

01:04:41.139 --> 01:04:44.110
known to the women,
has high status,

01:04:44.110 --> 01:04:47.929
is herself using contraception,
thinks it's a wonderful thing,

01:04:47.929 --> 01:04:50.862
you train her how to deal not
only with the woman but the

01:04:50.862 --> 01:04:52.800
woman has very little power
there,

01:04:52.800 --> 01:04:55.309
to deal with the husband,
to deal especially with the

01:04:55.309 --> 01:04:57.364
mother-in-law,
and for that you need a high

01:04:57.364 --> 01:05:00.143
status woman that can go into a
house and start discussing these

01:05:00.143 --> 01:05:03.467
things,
because even talking about

01:05:03.467 --> 01:05:09.577
anything to do with sex or
reproduction is not a socially

01:05:09.577 --> 01:05:11.760
acceptable thing.
 

01:05:11.760 --> 01:05:19.423
They started this program and
initially you got this kind of a

01:05:19.423 --> 01:05:20.429
thing.
 

01:05:20.429 --> 01:05:24.186
Veena Siddharth talked about
this, that when you start a

01:05:24.186 --> 01:05:27.853
family planning program,
this is an older version of the

01:05:27.853 --> 01:05:31.210
family planning program not the
one I've just described.

01:05:31.210 --> 01:05:35.101
What you see is they
took--there was a place called

01:05:35.101 --> 01:05:38.025
Matlab,
one of the districts in

01:05:38.025 --> 01:05:40.503
Bangladesh,
and they chose some villages,

01:05:40.503 --> 01:05:43.159
they wanted to know if what
they were doing was successful,

01:05:43.159 --> 01:05:45.559
some villages they gave this
family planning program to and

01:05:45.559 --> 01:05:48.590
other villages they didn't,
as a control region.

01:05:48.590 --> 01:05:52.039
Here is during this period up
until 1977 the comparison area

01:05:52.039 --> 01:05:54.380
where they didn't do anything
special.

01:05:54.380 --> 01:05:57.791
The government had a small
program but nothing much was

01:05:57.791 --> 01:05:58.550
happening.
 

01:05:58.550 --> 01:06:01.759
Now, the International
Diarrheal Research Group comes

01:06:01.759 --> 01:06:04.289
in with this somewhat updated
program,

01:06:04.289 --> 01:06:07.840
not the one I showed you,
and what happens immediately

01:06:07.840 --> 01:06:11.659
there's great success and
they're jumping up and down,

01:06:11.659 --> 01:06:16.545
okay this is true,
but then it peaks and then over

01:06:16.545 --> 01:06:18.639
time it falls down.
 

01:06:18.639 --> 01:06:22.389
What's happening here is a
small fraction of the women--

01:06:22.389 --> 01:06:25.117
well 20% is not terrible,
but a small fraction of the

01:06:25.117 --> 01:06:27.525
women,
before the program comes in,

01:06:27.525 --> 01:06:29.460
want to limit their births.
 

01:06:29.460 --> 01:06:32.530
You give them anything,
they accept it immediately.

01:06:32.530 --> 01:06:35.313
That this initial rise and
that's very standard for family

01:06:35.313 --> 01:06:36.289
planning programs.
 

01:06:36.289 --> 01:06:41.099
That you get an initial rise
and then it falls off,

01:06:41.099 --> 01:06:43.476
and over the long term if
you're evaluating the program

01:06:43.476 --> 01:06:46.980
here you think it's wonderful,
but if you're evaluating the

01:06:46.980 --> 01:06:49.690
program here it's kind of
worthless.

01:06:49.690 --> 01:06:53.193
Veena was talking about that,
that she comes out of this

01:06:53.193 --> 01:06:57.143
economic World Bank perspective
and they're very impressed with

01:06:57.143 --> 01:06:58.800
these periods of time.
 

01:06:58.800 --> 01:07:01.427
This is a program that,
in retrospect,

01:07:01.427 --> 01:07:05.402
we would say really didn't
work, although it helps a fair

01:07:05.402 --> 01:07:07.250
fraction of the women.
 

01:07:07.250 --> 01:07:10.668
Then you put in the good
program that I described to you

01:07:10.668 --> 01:07:12.833
and now what happens,
the later time,

01:07:12.833 --> 01:07:16.989
so we stop the previous--
the previous graph stopped in

01:07:16.989 --> 01:07:22.039
1977 at this level of
contraceptive acceptance,

01:07:22.039 --> 01:07:23.460
so they had a program that
didn't work,

01:07:23.460 --> 01:07:27.146
and then they start sending
these village working women into

01:07:27.146 --> 01:07:31.210
the homes of the other women and
now you get another big rise,

01:07:31.210 --> 01:07:32.610
that this is now successful
immediately,

01:07:32.610 --> 01:07:37.550
but now the success continues.
 

01:07:37.550 --> 01:07:41.440
Meanwhile there's modernization
and there's social diffusion

01:07:41.440 --> 01:07:44.293
that these areas,
the comparison areas are

01:07:44.293 --> 01:07:47.300
actually intermixed with the
treatment areas,

01:07:47.300 --> 01:07:50.409
and they hear a lot about
what's going on in there and so

01:07:50.409 --> 01:07:52.518
for that reason and others are
not--

01:07:52.518 --> 01:07:54.590
we don't really have data to
say why a rise,

01:07:54.590 --> 01:07:58.070
but even in the comparison area
it starts to rise.

01:07:58.070 --> 01:08:01.088
In one of your readings about
Taiwan where you have family

01:08:01.088 --> 01:08:03.260
planning, a very similar kind of
thing.

01:08:03.260 --> 01:08:05.719
It makes a big point that,
they did have some data,

01:08:05.719 --> 01:08:08.369
that they had villages where
they had a family planning

01:08:08.369 --> 01:08:10.489
program,
and then as soon as this was

01:08:10.489 --> 01:08:13.876
heard about in the surrounding
regions people would come into

01:08:13.876 --> 01:08:16.925
the treatment region to get
treatment so fertility goes

01:08:16.925 --> 01:08:17.488
down.
 

01:08:17.488 --> 01:08:26.949
One of the factors behind this
is certainly diffusion of the

01:08:26.949 --> 01:08:31.279
ideas of family planning.
 

01:08:31.279 --> 01:08:37.237
This thing in Bangladesh has
had terrible significance for

01:08:37.237 --> 01:08:43.300
what we believe about family
planning programs and people's

01:08:43.300 --> 01:08:47.180
acceptance of it,
because up until this time it

01:08:47.180 --> 01:08:50.560
was really dogma that you have
to have economic development and

01:08:50.560 --> 01:08:52.850
you have to have a degree of
literacy,

01:08:52.850 --> 01:08:56.747
and you have to have some
degree of women's status before

01:08:56.747 --> 01:08:59.880
people would want to limit their
fertility.

01:08:59.880 --> 01:09:04.189
Then you go into Bangladesh
with a well funded,

01:09:04.189 --> 01:09:07.373
well thought out,
well run program,

01:09:07.373 --> 01:09:09.810
and it starts working.
 

01:09:09.810 --> 01:09:13.680
Now Bangladesh is--its
fertility has kept falling and

01:09:13.680 --> 01:09:17.996
it's in there with a lot of
countries that are a lot richer

01:09:17.996 --> 01:09:18.890
than it.
 

01:09:18.890 --> 01:09:21.814
India is as lot richer,
Egypt is a lot richer than

01:09:21.814 --> 01:09:25.219
Bangladesh, and they all now
have come to more or less the

01:09:25.219 --> 01:09:27.189
same kind of fertility level.
 

01:09:27.189 --> 01:09:32.868
It now is no longer really
believed--

01:09:32.868 --> 01:09:35.859
it's believed that women almost
everywhere,

01:09:35.859 --> 01:09:38.974
in this case it must be the
men, because the men and the

01:09:38.974 --> 01:09:41.069
mother-in-law's control the
issue--

01:09:41.069 --> 01:09:43.134
really do want to reduce
fertility and if you give them

01:09:43.134 --> 01:09:48.729
the option,
they will accept it.

01:09:48.729 --> 01:09:54.868
Along the way other places have
learned other lessons,

01:09:54.868 --> 01:09:59.591
so India next door had a much
stronger central government

01:09:59.591 --> 01:10:03.881
because of the Gandhi effect,
Gandhi was such a national hero

01:10:03.881 --> 01:10:05.729
to all the ethnic groups in
India,

01:10:05.729 --> 01:10:09.020
so the government was strong
and Nehru was very strong,

01:10:09.020 --> 01:10:11.850
and Nehru's daughter
Mrs. Gandhi was very strong,

01:10:11.850 --> 01:10:15.448
and they were Westernized,
under the Malthusian influence,

01:10:15.448 --> 01:10:19.578
and they decided that they need
a family planning program also.

01:10:19.578 --> 01:10:24.818
Actually India was even before
this, but again they didn't know

01:10:24.818 --> 01:10:28.788
to do it, and they decided to
use incentives.

01:10:28.788 --> 01:10:30.270
That's when economists keep
telling us,

01:10:30.270 --> 01:10:31.788
every time you take an
economics course,

01:10:31.788 --> 01:10:35.520
people respond to incentives
and so they decided to use

01:10:35.520 --> 01:10:39.250
incentives to get people to take
on family planning.

01:10:39.250 --> 01:10:43.755
There's a lot of debate about
this issue of incentives and one

01:10:43.755 --> 01:10:47.298
part of it,
one article I read about people

01:10:47.298 --> 01:10:51.426
in villages in Nepal like the
one that Veena was in,

01:10:51.426 --> 01:10:52.560
pretty far.
 

01:10:52.560 --> 01:10:56.448
They have to take a whole day
off from work to go down to get

01:10:56.448 --> 01:10:58.653
a contraceptive,
then they have to go back,

01:10:58.653 --> 01:11:01.304
and what kind can they get,
because they can't go this

01:11:01.304 --> 01:11:03.408
every month to get something
new,

01:11:03.408 --> 01:11:06.988
and they can't take time off
from their work or their chores,

01:11:06.988 --> 01:11:09.868
so it's a real major economic
expense.

01:11:09.868 --> 01:11:13.445
Not the contraceptive itself,
but the time and effort needed

01:11:13.445 --> 01:11:16.719
if they have to take a bus,
it may be very expensive in

01:11:16.719 --> 01:11:17.810
their economy.
 

01:11:17.810 --> 01:11:26.150
So part of the idea of giving
incentives is to just repay the

01:11:26.150 --> 01:11:30.600
woman for her time and effort.
 

01:11:30.600 --> 01:11:33.631
India had started out that way
but the program was not very

01:11:33.631 --> 01:11:35.881
well run,
it wasn't--they didn't have the

01:11:35.881 --> 01:11:38.863
big international help that
Bangladesh had and the program

01:11:38.863 --> 01:11:41.396
wasn't terribly well run,
and so they sort of got

01:11:41.396 --> 01:11:44.051
frustrated at the results and
their population kept going and

01:11:44.051 --> 01:11:47.975
there was a time in India,
way before this current boom

01:11:47.975 --> 01:11:50.595
that India is--
has been going through,

01:11:50.595 --> 01:11:52.770
and may or may not still be
going through,

01:11:52.770 --> 01:11:56.064
and so the government got
frustrated and the population

01:11:56.064 --> 01:11:59.195
grew and they saw their hopes,
there's this window of

01:11:59.195 --> 01:12:02.140
opportunity that I was talking
about from modernization,

01:12:02.140 --> 01:12:04.689
if the population gets too
dense that window may close.

01:12:04.689 --> 01:12:11.203
The government got desperate
and started introducing some

01:12:11.203 --> 01:12:14.445
coercion,
some of it is incentive like

01:12:14.445 --> 01:12:17.877
transistor radios to the men--
to get the men to get

01:12:17.877 --> 01:12:20.787
sterilized and that was
wonderful but who got

01:12:20.787 --> 01:12:23.344
sterilized,
the old men that weren't going

01:12:23.344 --> 01:12:26.858
to have children anyway,
but I get a transistor radio or

01:12:26.858 --> 01:12:28.529
some money out of this.
 

01:12:28.529 --> 01:12:32.658
The whole thing crashed and it
came entangled as in America,

01:12:32.658 --> 01:12:36.658
reproduction and politics,
so the opposition to the--

01:12:36.658 --> 01:12:40.952
people didn't especially like
it because it's changing their

01:12:40.952 --> 01:12:41.680
culture.
 

01:12:41.680 --> 01:12:44.844
But, the opposition took hold
of it and blew up all the

01:12:44.844 --> 01:12:47.112
abuses,
no question there were abuses,

01:12:47.112 --> 01:12:50.063
blew up the abuses,
the newspapers blared the

01:12:50.063 --> 01:12:54.530
abuses and it became a very big
political thing and the Congress

01:12:54.530 --> 01:12:57.439
Party government fell because of
that.

01:12:57.439 --> 01:13:00.886
India has since sort of--then
they went through a period where

01:13:00.886 --> 01:13:04.109
they sort of did nothing in
family planning because it was

01:13:04.109 --> 01:13:07.104
in such bad favor and now
they've started up again and

01:13:07.104 --> 01:13:09.140
things are going a lot better.
 

01:13:09.140 --> 01:13:15.217
I think the story of this is
that the idea which was

01:13:15.217 --> 01:13:20.939
prevalent up until the
Bangladesh experiment,

01:13:20.939 --> 01:13:24.565
that only rich countries are
going to reduce their fertility

01:13:24.565 --> 01:13:28.332
is just plain wrong,
and now as the fertility

01:13:28.332 --> 01:13:32.523
transition goes through Asia,
